  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are international laws and frameworks designed to combat money laundering. The primary global organization addressing this issue is the Financial Action Task Force (FATF), which sets international standards for preventing money laundering and terrorist financing. Many countries have also implemented their own national anti-money laundering (AML) laws that comply with international guidelines. These laws typically require financial institutions to:\n\n1. Verify customer identities\n2. Monitor and report suspicious transactions\n3. Keep detailed financial records\n4. Implement compliance programs\n5. Cooperate with law enforcement investigations\n\nThe United Nations and International Monetary Fund also support global efforts to prevent money laundering.",
